        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 9:51AM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 950 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Northern Milan, or near Norwalk, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Pea-sized to half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lorain, Norwalk, Western Vermilion, Vermilion, Amherst, Milan,
Northern Milan, Sheffield, South Amherst, Monroeville, Berlin
Heights, and Birmingham.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
